OVERVIEW

Those files are rules that can be added to John the Ripper to support several hashes
format that OWADE can output.


REQUIREMENTS

Those files are made to work on an enhanced version of John the Ripper.
You can get it at <http://www.openwall.com/john>

The version we used to test it was john-1.7.8-jumbo2 with extra patches taken from
John's wiki: <http://openwall.info/wiki/john/patches>


INSTALL

Just add the files at the end of john.conf file.

For example:
$ cat credhist.conf >> $JOHN_HOME/john.conf

(you must first set the JOHN_HOME environment variable to John's run folder)


